---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { MAIN_SITE_URL } from "../site.config";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" locale="en">
  <article class="about">
    <p class="about__kicker">Colophon</p>
    <h1 class="about__title">About</h1>

    <div class="about__body report-prose">
      <p>
        <strong>civic-proof</strong> is a research site collecting the
        civic-proof series — long-form writing on digital identity, normative
        political theory, engineering design, and cross-jurisdictional
        governance.
      </p>

      <h2>Author</h2>

      <p>
        Written by <a href={MAIN_SITE_URL}>mashbean</a> (豆泥) during a
        Fellowship at the <a href="https://ash.harvard.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Allen Lab for Democracy Renovation</a>,
        Harvard Kennedy School Ash Center for Democratic Governance and
        Innovation (Spring 2026). Previously: Director of digital-wallet policy
        at Taiwan's Ministry of Digital Affairs (2022–2024); ICANN research
        fellow on DNS trust-root governance (2024–2025).
      </p>

      <h2>Research Question</h2>

      <p>
        The series takes up one animating question: can democratic societies
        design digital identity systems that preserve accountability without
        requiring citizens to identify themselves by name in advance? The
        answer developed across the series is conditionally affirmative —
        provided that the normative floor (the Public Realm Floor), the
        engineering bearings (wallet, agent delegation, civic receipts,
        selective-disclosure UX), and the governance structures (issuance
        legitimacy, exchange architecture, cross-jurisdictional redress) are
        designed conjunctively, not traded off.
      </p>

      <h2>Methodology — What Is and Isn't AI-Assisted</h2>

      <p>
        The research questions, framework choices, normative commitments, and
        case selections are the author's. Drafting and translation are
        AI-assisted using the <code>research-publishing-pipeline</code>
        (currently routed through Claude Opus 4.7), with citations and primary
        sources verified by the author. The foundational pieces (the 0'
        academic restatement, the Taiwan deep-dive, the AllenBridge essay) are
        human-reviewed; many of the empirical anchors are not yet, and are
        marked <strong>WIP</strong>.
      </p>

      <p>
        Translation note: the articles were originally written in Traditional
        Chinese and translated into formal academic English for this site.
        Chinese originals live at the <a href="/zh/">Chinese-language version
        of this site</a> (and at <a href="https://pro.mashbean.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">pro.mashbean.net</a>).
      </p>

      <h2>Citing this work</h2>

      <p>
        All articles are working papers and should be cited as such. URLs are
        stable; the canonical URL of each article is the appropriate citation
        target. The series is actively edited — refer to the <em>Updated</em>
        date on each article.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>

      <p>
        For correspondence, questions, or disagreements, the primary contact
        path is via <a href={MAIN_SITE_URL}>mashbean.net</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    width: 80%;
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-10);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  .about__kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
  }
  .about__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-6);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .about__body {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .about__body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: var(--space-7);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .about__body p { margin: 0 0 var(--space-5); text-wrap: pretty; }
  .about__body code { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.9em; padding: 1px 6px; background: var(--color-bg-muted); border-radius: 3px; }
  .about__body a { color: var(--color-ink); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  .about__body a:hover { text-decoration-thickness: 2px; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about { width: 90%; }
    .about__body { font-size: 1rem; }
  }
</style>
